# Enforce LF line endings for every text file on all platforms, independent of
# each developer's core.autocrlf. This is what `.prettierrc` (endOfLine: "lf")
# and the release `format:check` expect, so the working tree is deterministic on
# Windows and Linux alike. Binary assets are marked explicitly so Git never
# applies EOL normalization (or textual diffs/merges) to them.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Images
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.ico binary

# Fonts
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary

# Audio
*.ogg binary
*.mp3 binary
*.wav binary
*.m4a binary

# Video / Flash
*.mp4 binary
*.webm binary
*.mov binary
*.swf binary

# Archives / misc binaries
*.zip binary
*.pdf binary
